The paper focuses on the interface component of recommender systems and how it can support decision making and improve recommendation quality. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of implicit feedback for training recommendation systems, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions cognitive load and short-term memory, which could relate to the Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of movies as a test case, which could relate to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category if natural language processing techniques were used.
